header.gameNote: SUN BELT TOURNAMENT IN LAFAYETTE LA

article.description: Chrissy Givens scored 28 points to lead No. 17 Middle Tennessee to a 76-50 victory over Denver in the semifinals of the Sun Belt Conference tournament on Monday.
article.headline: No. 17 Middle Tennessee crushes Denver
article.linkText: Middle Tennessee rolls into Sun Belt semis
article.story:
LAFAYETTE, La. -- Chrissy Givens scored 28 points to lead Middle Tennessee (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today; No. 16 AP) to a 76-50 victory over Denver in the semifinals of the Sun Belt Conference tournament on Monday.

Givens' two layups and a 3-pointer during a 15-2 run gave the top-seeded Blue Raiders (28-3) a 29-9 lead with just under seven minutes left in the first half. Denver trailed 43-17 at halftime.

Middle Tennessee will play in Tuesday's conference final against Louisiana-Lafayette, which beat Arkansas State 62-59 in the other semifinal Monday.

The Blue Raiders, who've won all 20 games against Sun Belt opponents this season, extended their lead to 39 points when Jackie Pickel hit a 3-pointer to make it 65-26 early in the second half.

Nnenna Akotaobi led Denver (20-11) with 11 points.

Amber Holt had 15 points and 11 rebounds for Middle Tennessee, which outrebounded the Pioneers 44-24.

The Pioneers finished with 27 turnovers, which the Blue Raiders converted into 30 points.
